vered without skipping anything. Catching `UnsatisfiedLinkError` might be necessary if the native resource is missing. It’s crucial that the tests pass under the Native Image, asserting valid library loading or appropriate errors about missing resources. I need to ensure JUnit doesn’t fail due to missing metadata.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing agent-generated metadata**\\n\\nI’m looking into whether the test infrastructure's agent generates metadata from `javaTest`. It might include details about dynamic resource access, even if we only asked about tests initially. However, it seems the native image agent can include resources too. If it calls `StubLoader.getResourceAsStream`, there may be coverage for active classes and their resources. I think I might need a public test class and consider whether to remove placeholders while keeping the existing `JffiTest` placeholder, even if it doesn’t directly correspond to a class.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Deciding on file management**\\n\\nI'm contemplating whether to delete or keep a placeholder for JffiInitTest.java. I know we want a one-to-one mapping between report classes and test files. The existing generic approach seems unhelpful, and I could remove the placeholder or replace its contents. However, since I can't delete files directly, renaming could be a better option. If there are no tests left, creating a new one might also be necessary. Overall, it seems okay to delete unrelated placeholders that aren't beneficial.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Validating native image tests**\\n\\nI'm working on tests for the native image under the package com_github_jnr.jffi. My test, ComKenaiJffiInitTest, ensures that the default process library is available when loading the jffi stub. If it encounters an UnsatisfiedLinkError, I need to handle it by checking if there's a cause that points to a missing class or metadata issues, like ClassNotFoundException. It’s crucial to ensure that the class is reachable and properly registered to avoid reflection issues in the native image.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying class loading**\\n\\nIt seems that `Class.forName` can indeed load any class that is included, but there's a catch: if the class isn't statically reachable, it might not be included in the metadata. This makes me think about how agent metadata handles reflection. It’s important to ensure that the necessary classes are registered for reflection to avoid issues when trying to load them dynamically. I wonder what steps I might need to take to confirm class reachability.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_0igWDekkKlVrXkpugN6AMaiU|fc_017396f86f7fdf690169f806489ffc81949e0cc84599dcf556", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find ~/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/com.github.jnr/jffi/1.3.9 -maxdepth 2 -type f -name '*.pom' -o -name '*.jar' | sort | sed -n '1,80p'", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1434, "output": 1554, "cacheRead": 17920, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20908, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777862194498, "responseId": "resp_017396f86f7fdf690169f80632f0e08194b271243dd6c652ac"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_0igWDekkKlVrXkpugN6AMaiU|fc_017396f86f7fdf690169f806489ffc81949e0cc84599dcf556", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/home/vjovanov/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/com.github.jnr/jffi/1.3.9/163d683f80c06911f3e770c723d6e399e4c59448/jffi-1.3.9-native.jar\n/home/vjovanov/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/com.github.jnr/jffi/1.3.9/174c6ac29abb9e8303247a149453c51414799eec/jffi-1.3.9.pom\n/home/vjovanov/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/com.github.jnr/jffi/1.3.9/b776ea131fa693af2c943368b52acf94131cbd7/jffi-1.3.9.jar\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777862216964}]}
