t that sets system properties for loading a library. I need to create an empty directory for the library path and target file. If the `Library.getDefault()` method fails, I want to confirm that it throws an `UnsatisfiedLinkError`. But I’m wondering if class initialization for `Library` might access `Foreign.VERSION_MAJOR` before `getDefault()` is called, which could cause a failure. The challenge is whether `assertThrows()` can even catch an `ExceptionInInitializerError` when `Library` fails to load.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering dependency issues**\\n\\nI’m thinking that I probably can’t use reflection directly in this context. Instead, I might need to rely on AssertJ, which seems like it could already be part of my dependencies. It's important not to use reflection if I can avoid it, to keep things cleaner and more straightforward. So, I’ll focus on what AssertJ offers and how I can leverage it in my tests without getting into more complex reflection-based solutions!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_NIvjhrbcbhPvTsoRRHQO9lyi|fc_017396f86f7fdf690169f8066c8d7881948aaa905623b570ac", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rm tests/src/com.github.jnr/jffi/1.3.9/src/test/java/com_github_jnr/jffi/JffiTest.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1011, "output": 1412, "cacheRead": 24576, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 26999, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777862233091, "responseId": "resp_017396f86f7fdf690169f806598db08194b23afb35547cdc79"}}
